{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017adC8jYqHabjfHN8CjGiJe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016YVRPM5htmyHvxMfVQYiVd","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\n## Review Date: 2026-06-25\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n### Deployments\n\n| Resource    | Replicas | Image                  |\n|-------------|----------|------------------------|\n| ray-head    | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0   |\n| ray-worker  | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0   |\n\n### Resource Requests / Limits\n\nBoth \\`ray-head\\` and \\`ray-worker\\` containers have \\`resources: {}\\` — no CPU or\nmemory requests or limits are set on either deployment.\n\n### ray-head Launch Command\n\n\\`\\`\\`\nray start --head --node-ip-address=\\\"\\${MY_POD_IP}\\\" --port=6379 \\\\\n  --include-dashboard=false --num-cpus=0 --block\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nThe Ray dashboard is **disabled** (\\`--include-dashboard=false\\`).\n\n### ray-worker Launch Command\n\n\\`\\`\\`\nray start --address=ray-head:6379 --node-ip-address=\\\"\\${MY_POD_IP}\\\" \\\\\n  --num-cpus=1 --block\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Services\n\n\\`ray-head\\` is a **ClusterIP** service exposing only the GCS port:\n\n| Service   | Type      | Port(s)   | Notes                        |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------|------------------------------|\n| ray-head  | ClusterIP | 6379/TCP  | GCS only; no dashboard port  |\n\nNo NodePort or LoadBalancer service exists. The dashboard port (8265) is not\nexposed anywhere.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Changes for the Next Upgrade Window\n\n### 2a. Image Upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\nUpgrade both head and worker containers to \\`rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\` to pick up\nbug fixes and minor feature improvements.\n\n### 2b. Worker Scale-Out: 1 → 3 Replicas\n\nIncrease \\`ray-worker\\` replicas from 1 to 3 to provide additional compute\ncapacity and basic redundancy against single-worker failure.\n\n### 2c. Set Resource Requests and Limits\n\nAdd explicit CPU/memory requests and limits so the Kubernetes scheduler can bin-pack\nefficiently and the Kubelet can enforce resource isolation. Proposed values:\n\n**ray-head:**\n- requests: cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\n- limits:   cpu=2,    memory=4Gi\n\n**ray-worker:**\n- requests: cpu=1,    memory=2Gi\n- limits:   cpu=4,    memory=8Gi\n\n### 2d. Enable and Expose the Ray Dashboard\n\nEnable the Ray dashboard on the head node (port 8265) and add a NodePort service\nso team members can reach it from outside the cluster for observability.\n\n- Change \\`--include-dashboard=false\\` → \\`--include-dashboard=true\\` and add\n  \\`--dashboard-port=8265\\` to the ray-head startup command.\n- Add container port 8265 to the ray-head pod spec.\n- Add port 8265 to the ray-head Service (or create a separate dashboard Service).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Exact kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — for review only)\n\n### Step 1: Upgrade images on both deployments\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-worker ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 2: Scale ray-worker to 3 replicas\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=3\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 3: Set resource requests/limits on ray-head\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\":\\\"replace\\\",\\\"path\\\":\\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\":{\n     \\\"requests\\\":{\\\"cpu\\\":\\\"500m\\\",\\\"memory\\\":\\\"1Gi\\\"},\n     \\\"limits\\\":{\\\"cpu\\\":\\\"2\\\",\\\"memory\\\":\\\"4Gi\\\"}\n   }}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 4: Set resource requests/limits on ray-worker\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-worker --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\":\\\"replace\\\",\\\"path\\\":\\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\":{\n     \\\"requests\\\":{\\\"cpu\\\":\\\"1\\\",\\\"memory\\\":\\\"2Gi\\\"},\n     \\\"limits\\\":{\\\"cpu\\\":\\\"4\\\",\\\"memory\\\":\\\"8Gi\\\"}\n   }}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 5: Enable dashboard in ray-head command and add container port\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\":\\\"replace\\\",\\\"path\\\":\\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/command\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\":[\\\"sh\\\",\\\"-c\\\",\n     \\\"ray start --head --node-ip-address=\\\\\\\"\\${MY_POD_IP}\\\\\\\" --port=6379 --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-port=8265 --num-cpus=0 --block\\\\n\\\"]},\n  {\\\"op\\\":\\\"add\\\",\\\"path\\\":\\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/ports/-\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\":{\\\"containerPort\\\":8265,\\\"name\\\":\\\"dashboard\\\",\\\"protocol\\\":\\\"TCP\\\"}}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 6: Expose the dashboard via NodePort\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch svc ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\":\\\"add\\\",\\\"path\\\":\\\"/spec/ports/-\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"dashboard\\\",\\\"port\\\":8265,\\\"targetPort\\\":8265,\\\"protocol\\\":\\\"TCP\\\"}},\n  {\\\"op\\\":\\\"replace\\\",\\\"path\\\":\\\"/spec/type\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"NodePort\\\"}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 7: Verify rollout completion\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray get pods -o wide\nkubectl -n ray get svc ray-head\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Procedure\n\nIf issues arise after applying the changes, roll back to the previous ReplicaSet:\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=1\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Pre-Change Checklist\n\n- [ ] Confirm \\`rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\` image is available and tested in staging.\n- [ ] Verify the cluster has sufficient CPU/memory headroom for 3 workers with the\n      new resource limits (3 x 4 CPU + 8 Gi = 12 CPU + 24 Gi worker capacity).\n- [ ] Notify users of a brief GCS reconnect when the head pod is replaced.\n- [ ] Confirm no production jobs are running before applying head-node changes.\n- [ ] After the change, verify the dashboard is reachable at the NodePort and\n      that all 3 workers appear in the cluster nodes view.\n\"\n","description":"Create the change-plan ConfigMap with the migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2840,"cache_read_input_tokens":29924,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2840},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b982125b-7a0d-4a8e-b615-cbdccae27104","uuid":"14f247eb-d958-477f-bd94-2cd656842775","request_id":"req_011CcPxSyd5LgfCsJbDYMxQw"}
